== Application limits == <!--T:12-->
It must be taken into account that the obtained results represented in the graphs must be inside the application limits of the method. 

The application limits of the Blount and Fox correction method are:
<center>
<math> F_\Delta \geq 1.0 </math>

<math> \frac{LCG}{L_P} \leq 0.46 </math>
</center>
Where:

* <math> F_\Delta </math> is the volumetric Froude number, defined by the following expression:
<center>
<math> F_\Delta = \frac{V}{\sqrt{g\nabla^{\frac{1}{3}}}} </math>
</center>
* <math> LCG </math> is the longitudinal center of gravity of the vessel.
* <math> L_P </math> is the projected keel length of the vessel.

These limits extend the application of the Savitsky method to low-speed conditions.

== Usage == <!--T:13-->
This tool does not have a strict dependency on a '''Ship instance'''(see [[Ship_CreateShip|Ship CreateShip]]), which means that it is possible to use it introducing the necessary ship data values in the dialogue.

